# makepkg.conf patch for mold linker and optimizations
# WHY: Faster linking with mold, optimized compilation for AMD Ryzen 5600X3D
# WHAT: LDFLAGS and RUSTFLAGS changes for native CPU
# HOW: Apply with: sudo patch /etc/makepkg.conf < makepkg.conf.patch
#      Or manually edit /etc/makepkg.conf
#
# NOTE: This is documentation only; actual patch requires user customization
# based on their specific makepkg.conf version.
#
# Recommended changes:
#
# 1. LDFLAGS - Add mold linker:
#    LDFLAGS="-Wl,-O1 -Wl,--sort-common -Wl,--as-needed -Wl,-z,relro -Wl,-z,now -fuse-ld=mold"
#
# 2. RUSTFLAGS - Add native CPU optimization and mold:
#    RUSTFLAGS="-C opt-level=3 -C target-cpu=native -C link-arg=-fuse-ld=mold"
#
# 3. MAKEFLAGS - Use all cores:
#    MAKEFLAGS="-j$(nproc)"
#
# Dependencies:
#   - mold: Fast linker (optdepend of this package)
#   - Install with: yay -S mold
